<br>
Later I get the tell from the druid apologizing and saying that she's new to the game (level 34) and hasnt really gotten the hang of it yet. And that she's sorry to have offended me and caused me to leave. At which I point I replied that I'm not mad. I just didnt want to stay grouped if it meant me getting killed, repeatedly. I also told her that I didnt want to tell her point by point how to play her class because I had already told her to snare the mobs at 50% and please med instead of melee. She apologized again. <br>
<br>
At this point, I thought she was really trying to make up so I decided to give it a shot. I asked her if she would like some pointers. I gave her some advice, mainly just remembering how druids used to play when I grouped with them. I basically told her to med instead of melee, dont nuke as much, and heal a little more, and damage shield the tank so he can hold arggo better. She goes &quot;ok.&quot; Then 5 mins later she sends me a tell saying that: maybe if people like you wouldnt leave the group, then poeple like me wouldnt play as badly&quot;<br>
<br>
At this point, I'm boggled beyond belief. She was trying to blame ME for her playing badly....I told her as much. Dont blame me, you never asked for help and I did not want to talk down to you by telling you how to play your class. People are so odd <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-Chosun- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uridalestarwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ridale Starwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/1/02 1:30:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=568.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Try...</span><hr size=1> I got a  Wizard to 46 on another server.   In groups one of best spells Wizard can toss is Stun.  If no &quot;slower&quot; is in group then &quot;Bonds of Force&quot; first followed by stun.   1 nuke at the end.  Only Burn in emergency.<br>
<br>
Stun may not be a fun as nuking the bejesus out things,  but it saves the cleric on healing tanks. I would cast stun much much more than Nuke when grouped.<br>
<br>
I did not learn this on my own.  Other players taught me how to play wizard in groups too.  No mater how much you think you know the game, someone may have a better way to do things so Tactful advice is always welcome by me.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 333<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/1/02 1:32:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=568.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Try...</span><hr size=1> Chosun:<br>
<br>
Is it possible you misinterpreted her as blaming you?  Maybe she meant, &quot;If you'd just told me I wasn't being as effective as I could be, I'd have learned to play better.&quot;  Or, maybe she was just knee-jerking.  Who knows?<br>
<br>
In any event, I'm a druid who still melees in groups.  If I'm full on mana (and Shield of Brambles/Ensnare don't cost that much), and I've already cast the spells I typically cast at the beginning of a combat, I'll wade in.  There's really no point in meditating when one's at full mana.<br>
<br>
I wasn't aware that damage shields influenced who had aggro.  That hasn't been my experience...  It registers as &quot;non-melee&quot; damage for the purposes of experience (outside of groups), and plenty of creatures have moved off of a damage-shielded tank in my group to attack a non-damage-shielded meleer whose drawn aggro onto her-/himself.<br>
<br>
